Module 20 ‚Äî Basic Data Types: Boolean

Author: Peyman Miyandashti
Year: 2025

Booleans are one of the most important and powerful basic data types in Python.
A boolean can only represent two values: True or False.
Even though it looks simple, the boolean type is the foundation of all logic, conditions, decision making, and program flow in Python.

In this module, I focus on understanding how booleans work, how Python creates them, and how I can use them to make my programs think and behave intelligently.

By the end of this module, I should feel confident using booleans in real code:
from small conditions to more realistic examples involving comparisons, decisions, validations, and control flow.

